==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Smalt
<hw>Smalt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. <ets>smalto</ets>,
LL. <ets>smaltum</ets>; of Teutonic origin; cf. OHG. <ets>smalz</ets>
grease, butter, G. <ets>schmalz</ets> grease, OHG. <ets>smelzan</ets> to
melt, G. <ets>schmelzen</ets>. See <er>Smelt</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, and
cf. <er>Amel</er>, <er>Enamel</er>.]</ety> <def>A deep blue pigment or
coloring material used in various arts. It is a vitreous substance made
of cobalt, potash, and calcined quartz fused, and reduced to a
powder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smalt-blue</ent>⟦br⟧
